  "page": "Iron Chronicle",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <i><b>Iron Chronicle</b></i> is a work which includes the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> control of the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> prior to <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>. The book states that <a href=\"/index.php/Harwyn_Hardhand\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Harwyn Hardhand\">Harwyn Hardhand</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Isles_and_the_Rivers\" title=\"King of the Isles and the Rivers\">King of the Isles and the Rivers</a>, would pit his <a href=\"/index.php/Bannermen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bannermen\">bannermen</a> against each other in order to keep them weak.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Iron_Chronicle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_riverlands:_house_tully.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Riverlands: House Tully.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limi